s midmanhattan office where he worked as chief operating officer of the prestigious kpmg accounting firm nowadays siboni is driving himself around silicon valley chalk it up to the fact that at age  siboni reached an epiphany  thats the name of the palo alto software firm he joins this month as chairman and chief executive im trading salary and the trappings of power for equity siboni said epiphany sells a  software package that can extract customer information from any database and pour it into a web browser the idea is to let marketing people spot occasional customers and turn them into big spenders latest business videos using software to pump up sales is a top priority for corporations like charles schwab corp which has been using epiphany since november theres nothing on the market that im aware of that is as powerful and as easy to use and is also webaccessible said mary kelley vice president for database marketing at schwab credit for making epiphany powerful and simple goes to co founders ben wegbreit and steve blank and lead programmers greg walsh and john mccaskey now its up to siboni to sell this startup to the fortune  by drawing on personal relationships built up during two decades as a highprofile kpmg consultant siboni is no stranger to the valley he started kpmgs high tech consulting practice in  advising ancient firms such as wordstar last year while coo at kpmg siboni took sides in the browser wars when he handed a huge contract to microsoft despite a personal sales pitch from netscape ceo jim barksdale over lunch in palo alto siboni said hes run into barksdale since then and their cordial exchange convinced him that the netscape ceo hasnt held a grudge in fact barksdales such a big man he probably doesnt mind that epiphany just hired karen richardson as its vice president of sales luring her away from a similar post at netscape after all its only business in the fast lane  conspicuous absence house speaker newt gingrich led a delegation of congressional republicans on a meetandgreet tour of silicon valley this week but local representative tom campbell rcampbell was not a member of his party could it be the hometowner was snubbed because he was on the losing side of last summers attempted republican coup against the speaker whatever the cause campbell finds himself temporarily frozen out of the gops effort to make sure vice president al gore doesnt walk away with silicon valley votes  or money we want to pay more attention here and ask in return for more attention to be paid to us said representative bob goodlatte rva who accompanied gingrich goodlatte who has spearheaded encryption legislation favored by hightech firms was tapped by gingrich to head a new technology leadership group that will bring republicans in congress together with industry leaders like cisco vice president judy estrin merrill lynch investment banker scott ryles and kleiner perkins venture capitalist floyd kvamme  aols slippery slope last week america online shut down the web site of a member who had parodied several passages from the koran the shutdown was publicized by the freedom forum a virginia foundation dedicated to newspaper and first amendment issues the forum said the site drew strong objections from muslim academics in egypt and elsewhere berkeleybased aol watcher dave cassel said members at large hardly noticed the flap but cassel questioned aols censorship policy in light of the fact that a texas ku klux klan chapter has a longstanding aol page that advises visitors to prepare for the coming disorder that will test the very survival of the white race    against the jack booted zionist occupational government aol spokeswoman tricia primrose said her firm received more than  complaints about the koran site and closed it after decided it defamed a religious group she said aol had received some complaints last year about the kkk site and aol requested some changes to the page at that time but this year aol has not heard any objections from members and therefore has not taken any action against the page the page is maintained by the klan group that marched in jasper texas last week thats the town where a black man was killed by being dragged behind a truck allegedly driven by several white men latest from the sfgate homepageclick below for the top news from around the bay area and beyond sign up for our newsletters to be the first to learn about breaking news and more go to sign in and manage profile at the top of the page the trump presidency trump fires off volley of angry early morning tweets trump claims he has complete power to pardon opinion sessions meeting with russian official not normal trump commissions uss gerald r ford latest news ‘home alone’ actor dies at  in palo alto hotel golfer shoots lowest score ever at major championship streetscape improvements bad for business sf merchants say berkeley man gets  years to life for human trafficking more than  animals removed from  homes  local spots may join national historic register richmond mayor witnessed attack outside bart station sf stabbing victim idd as yearold city resident  american towns you havent heard of but should visit asap our favorite mustsee small towns in northern california  great bay area hikes that end with a beer  spots where bay area kids can experience the great outdoors all the things bay area athletes should do before they die the coolest thing to do in each bay area city seattle wilderness getaway among worlds most expensive this couple gave up their sf apartments to travel in a van how the pony express linked an isolated sf to the country barbary coast raid brought sf’s bad old days to an end todays top picks game of thrones star lists sherman oaks home for m  clever ways to kick your kids off their screens this summer the island ghost town in the middle of the sf bay most popular  a mini gold rush has descended on northern california  dear abby dad can’t be thanked enough for helping pay bills  allincl